James de Villiers, News24 Roads have been closed around Nyanga Junction where an apparent attempted cash in transit heist turned into a hostage drama. (Supplied) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town - Police are combing the Shoprite supermarket in Nyanga Junction for any suspects in connection to a hostage drama that played out in the store on Monday afternoon.It is undetermined how many robbers were involved in the hostage and if some robbers managed to fled the scene or is still inside the building, police spokesperson Novela Potelwa said in a statement.A 25-year-old suspect has been arrested and several people released.The suspect, a security guard, was injured during a shoot-out with security personnel.He is in a critical condition in a nearby hospital, Potelwa said.No additional injuries have been reported. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.